olive oil
2 potato
½ Onion
1 egg
1 packet lamb mince
1 packet fine breadcrumbs
1 sachet Garlic & Herb Seasoning
1 tbs balsamic vinegar
1 tsp brown sugar
2 Burger Bun
1 packet Slaw Mix
1 packet Dill & Parsley Mayonnaise
drizzle white wine vinegar
1 packet Grated Parmesan Cheese

• Preheat oven to 240°C/220°C fan-forced. Cut potato into wedges and place on a lined oven tray.
• Drizzle with olive oil, season with salt and toss to coat. Bake until tender, 20-25 minutes.
• In the last 5 minutes of cook time, remove potatoes from oven. Sprinkle with grated Parmesan cheese and bake until golden and crispy.

• While the wedges are baking, thinly slice red onion.
• In a large bowl, combine the egg, lamb mince, fine breadcrumbs, garlic & herb seasoning and a pinch of pepper.
• Shape lamb mixture into patties (1 per person), slightly larger than your burger buns.

TIP: Make a shallow indent in centre of each patty to help prevent it puffing up as it cooks.

• In a large frying pan, heat a drizzle of olive oil over medium-high heat. Cook onion, stirring, until softened, 5-6 minutes.
• Reduce heat to medium. Add the balsamic vinegar, brown sugar and a splash of water and mix well. Cook until dark and sticky, 3-5 minutes. Transfer to a bowl.

• Wipe out and return frying pan to a medium-high heat with a drizzle of olive oil. Cook lamb patties until just cooked through, 4-5 minutes on each side.

• While patties are cooking, halve burger buns and bake directly on a wire oven rack until heated through, 2-3 minutes.
• Meanwhile, in a medium bowl, combine slaw mix, dill & parsley mayo, a drizzle of white wine vinegar and a pinch of salt.

• Top burger bun bases with caramelised onion, a lamb patty and some slaw.
• Serve with cheesy wedges. Enjoy!